#: of numpy.fft.irfft:78
msgid "The inverse of the two-dimensional FFT of real input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:79
msgid ":obj:`irfftn`"
msgstr ":obj:`irfftn`"

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:80
msgid "The inverse of the *n*-dimensional FFT of real input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:84
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:85
msgid ""
"Returns the real valued `n`-point inverse discrete Fourier transform of `a`, "
"where `a` contains the non-negative frequency terms of a Hermitian-symmetric "
"sequence. `n` is the length of the result, not the input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:90
msgid ""
"If you specify an `n` such that `a` must be zero-padded or truncated, the "
"extra/removed values will be added/removed at high frequencies. One can thus "
"resample a series to `m` points via Fourier interpolation by: ``a_resamp = "
"irfft(rfft(a), m)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:95
msgid ""
"The correct interpretation of the hermitian input depends on the length of "
"the original data, as given by `n`. This is because each input shape could "
"correspond to either an odd or even length signal. By default, `irfft` "
"assumes an even output length which puts the last entry at the Nyquist "
"frequency; aliasing with its symmetric counterpart. By Hermitian symmetry, "
"the value is thus treated as purely real. To avoid losing information, the "
"correct length of the real input **must** be given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:105
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.irfft:116
msgid ""
"Notice how the last term in the input to the ordinary `ifft` is the complex "
"conjugate of the second term, and the output has zero imaginary part "
"everywhere.  When calling `irfft`, the negative frequencies are not "
"specified, and the output array is purely real."
msgstr ""

